  m_Name: Pes_Distal_Phalanx_D3_R
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Pes_Distal_Phalanx_D3_R
  partName: Pes Distal Phalanx D3 Right
  descriptionChunks:
  - The right distal phalanx of the third hind digit forms the terminal portion of
    the toe and supports the claw structure within the canine hindpaw. This bone
    contributes to traction, stability, and coordinated toe movement during locomotion
    and weight-bearing activities.
  - Tendons attached to the distal phalanx allow controlled digital flexion and extension
    while maintaining balanced hindpaw mechanics. The third digit is particularly
    important for support and propulsion during walking and running. Proper alignment
    and structural health are necessary for efficient movement and stable ground
    contact.
